O God! Thou art my God alone;  
In silent awe my heart is shown.  
No riches, power, or earthly fame,  
Can match the glory of Thy name.  
When I am lost, Thy path is clear;  
Thy gentle call I always hear.  
In darkest night and brightest day,  
You guide my steps, You lead the way.  
O God! Thou art my God alone;  
In every breath, Thy grace is known.

Light breaks where no sun shines;
In the hush between each thought,
A gentle pulse, a secret sign,
From nothingness is wrought.

It spills in places undefined,
Where sorrow lingers long;
And though the world remains confined,
It hums a brighter song.

Within the hollow, hope is found;
Within the lost, a spark;
For even where the night is crowned,
Light dances in the dark.
